CatDescriptText: Richard Beitel, engineer, Pleasant Hills and Frank Pasquinelli, salesman, Castle Shannon were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, November 19, 1960, pg. C1 with question "Why do you think Negroes voted so heavily for Senator John F. Kennedy, Democrat, for President, in last Tuesday's election?" Mr. Beitel's answer reads: "I think the Negroes merely returned to the Democratic column where they have been since the days of Franklin Delano Roosevelt." Mr. Pasquinelli's answer reads: "I would not know, because I'm not familiar with the breakdown of the voting"
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Richard Beitel wearing striped necktie and eyeglasses, standing in front of store window; Portrait of Frank Pasquinelli wearing striped scarf and hat, standing in front of store window with young boy
